We start from the initial fixed‐asset value as recorded on 2023‑12‑31. In our records that transaction (type “Fixed Assets”) shows an initial amount of 5,000,000.00.

Then we scan for any additional fixed‐asset purchases. In our data the purchases are recorded with type “Fixed Assets Purchase” (all with the same prefix “FixedAsset20231231001”). We find these five transactions:

1. 256,859.19 (Processing Equipment4)  
2. 171,985.91 (Storage Facilities5)  
3. 55,577.41 (Production Line6)  
4. 117,840.57 (Production Line7)  
5. 73,932.79 (Production Line8)

Summing these additions:
  256,859.19 + 171,985.91 = 428,845.10  
  428,845.10 + 55,577.41 = 484,422.51  
  484,422.51 + 117,840.57 = 602,263.08  
  602,263.08 + 73,932.79 = 676,195.87

So the total amount of new fixed assets purchased is 676,195.87.

The gross fixed assets at “end” would then be the sum of the initial value plus the additions:
  5,000,000.00 + 676,195.87 = 5,676,195.87

Next we look for depreciation. In our data there is one depreciation transaction:
  45748.43 (the “Depreciation20240101001” entry).

Subtracting depreciation gives the net fixed assets at the end:
  5,676,195.87 – 45,748.43 = 5,630,447.44

Thus we report:

• Fixed assets net Initial Value = 5,000,000.00  
• Fixed assets net End Value = 5,630,447.44
